    {"id": "ja_fd_062", "levels": [{"front": "hungry", "back": "お腹が空いた / 空腹な", "romanized": "onaka ga suita / kūfuku na", "grammarNote": "In Japanese, hunger is expressed as a physical state: 'onaka ga suita' (お腹が空いた) literally means 'my stomach has become empty'. Similarly, thirst: 'nodo ga kawaita' (喉が渇いた) = 'my throat became dry'. These are transitory states, not personality traits."}, {"front": "I'm hungry. Are you thirsty?", "back": "お腹が空きました。喉が渇いていますか？", "romanized": "onaka ga sukimashita. nodo ga kawaite imasu ka", "literal": "Stomach [subj] empty-became. Throat [subj] dried-is?"}]},
